<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRENTWOOD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 As a long-time Brentwood resident who lives less than three blocks and well 
within helicopter and lookie-loo harassment from O.J. Simpson's house, I have 
one question: 
</P>
<P>
 In reporting in the tremendous inconvenience those of us who are neighbors 
have endured (July 13), what in heaven's name possessed you to print the most 
detailed yet map of exactly how to get here? As I went about my business today, 
I saw many more "visitors" than I have seen over the last few days. 
</P>
<P>
 CAROL JANES 
</P>
<P>
 LOS ANGELES 
</P>
<P>
 I am so sick of Brentwood homeowners whining about tourists in their 
neighborhood.One has to wonder -- if only the Brentwood homeowners had been 
half as vigilant to their streets and surrounding community before this brutal 
double slaying occurred, then perhaps they would have been able to detect the 
crime before it happened, and even somehow prevented it. 
</P>
<P>
 It's too late to peer through your mini-blinds and hedges calling the cops 
every few minutes, Brentwood residents. Just be thankful that you're still 
alive to see it. Two former residents, Nicole Brown Simpson and Ron Goldman, 
aren't so lucky. 
</P>
<P>
 LUCY D. NARKUS 
</P>
<P>
 Glendale 
</P>
