<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / THE FINAL; SPOTLIGHT; PLAY WAS GOLDEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BILL DWYRE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The World Cup Golden Ball Award, presented to the outstanding player of the 
tournament as voted by more than 1,000 members of the international press, went 
to Romario of Brazil. He had more than 2,400 points, well ahead of Italy's 
Baggio, who was second with 1,500 and received the Silver Ball, and Bronze Ball 
winner Hristo Stoitchkov of Bulgaria. BILL DWYRE 
</P>
</TEXT>
