<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / THE FINAL; SPOTLIGHT; UNITED FOR ITALY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BILL PLASCHKE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Perhaps nothing was more representative of the World Cup's effect in Los 
Angeles than a 1981 pickup truck parked outside the soccer field at Loyola 
Marymount on Saturday morning. 
</P>
<P>
 Sitting on the roof, in hopes of catching a glimpse of the Italian team over 
the fence, were a fan from Mexico, two Italians from Walnut and two Italian 
fans from Canada. 
</P>
<P>
 None had laid eyes on each other. 
</P>
<P>
 "I have been gone from Italy 20 years. This is the first time I see this team. 
I am so nervous just sitting," said Natalino Urbani, from Walnut. 
</P>
<P>
 Said Luis Haro: "I let them sit on my truck because, with Mexico losing, I am 
now for the underdog." BILL PLASCHKE 
</P>
