<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / THE FINAL; SPOTLIGHT; AND THIS EVENT MADE HOW MANY 
MILLIONS? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RANDY HARVEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 For the coin toss preceding the 30-minute overtime Sunday, referee Sandor Puhl 
of Hungary found himself a dollar short. 
</P>
<P>
 More specifically, he was unable to find the silver dollar specially minted 
for such occasions in the World Cup. 
</P>
<P>
 But David Simmons, Rose Bowl venue director, came to the rescue, lending him 
an ordinary quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 It did the job. Italy won the toss, the game proceeded but Simmons didn't get 
his quarter back. RANDY HARVEY 
</P>
