<TEXT>
<P>
 How well did World Cup '94 do financially? 
</P>
<P>
 Well, that will take months to determine, but according to sources Sunday, 
there were a couple of indications that this event ended up with loads of black 
ink. 
</P>
<P>
 Saturday night's Three Tenors concert at Dodger Stadium, sponsored by the 
World Cup, generated $12.2 million in gross revenue. Sunday's World Cup final 
at the Rose Bowl, between Brazil and Italy, generated slightly more than $45 
million. BILL DWYRE 
</P>
