WORLD CUP USA '94 / THE FINAL; SPOTLIGHT; ADDING INSULT TO INJURY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 As if losing the World Cup to Brazil wasn't bad enough, the Italians are 
missing cash, jewelry and other items. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities in Warren Township, N.J., said the rooms of Roberto Baggio and 12 
of his teammates at the Somerset Hills Hotel were broken into while the team 
was beating Bulgaria, 2-1, in the semifinals at Giants Stadium on Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 About $30,000 in cash was taken, along with watches and sunglasses, Somerset 
County Prosecutor Nicholas Bissell Jr. said. 
</P>
