<HEADLINE>
<P>
HARD COURT TENNIS EVENT STARTS TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Men's National 50-50 Hard Court tennis championships will begin today at 
the Lindborg Racquet Club. 
</P>
<P>
 The tournament gets under way with singles play today.Doubles start Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 The draw will have 64 players entered in singles and 32 teams in doubles in 
each of the two age divisions. Semifinals will be Friday with singles finals on 
Saturday and doubles finals on Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 James Parker of Houston is the top-seeded player in the 50-and-over singles 
division. Alex Olmeda of Los Angeles is seeded No. 1 in 55 singles. Parker and 
Ken Robinson of San Carlos are seeded first in 50 doubles. Jim Nelson of Irvine 
and Bob Duesler of Newport Beach are the top-seeded team in 55 doubles. 
</P>
<P>
 The event is sanctioned by the U.S. Tennis Assn. 
</P>
