<P>
BAY AREA TRAIN WORKERS SET TO STRIKE AFTER REJECTING OFFER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Bay Area Rapid Transit District train operators and station agents rejected 
the rail system's latest contract offer Sunday night, just hours before a 
strike deadline. 
</P>
<P>
 The Amalgamated Transit Union Local 1555 voted against the pact, 338 to 12, 
according to union spokeswoman Colleen McCarthy. The vote followed one earlier 
in the week that saw the 71-mile rail line's clerks and maintenance workers 
vote down the proposal. 
</P>
