<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: THOUSAND OAKS; MAN SOUGHT IN RESTAURANT HOLDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 East county sheriff's deputies are looking for a heavy-set, Caucasian man who 
held up a Domino's Pizza outlet in Thousand Oaks at gunpoint and clubbed an 
employee with a telephone receiver before cleaning out the cash register. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators said the suspect, who weighs about 230 pounds and is about 6 
feet, 3 inches tall, pointed a handgun at employee Mark Robertson, 19, as he 
was returning from a delivery minutes before midnight Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Robertson and the suspect both entered the store at 290 Moorpark Road, and the 
suspect ordered another employee, Farrokh Iranshahr, 49, to open the safe. 
</P>
<P>
 When Iranshahr refused to open the safe, the suspect clubbed him with a 
telephone receiver and grabbed the cash from the register, fleeing with an 
undisclosed amount of money, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Iranshahr was treated at the scene for a cut ear. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators said the suspect is between 19 and 23 years old, with brown hair 
and a goatee. JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
