THEFTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARY F. POLS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A series of thefts from the parking lot at The Oaks mall has led Ventura 
County Crime Stoppers to offer a $1,000 reward for information helping to 
identify the thieves. 
</P>
<P>
 Sheriff's investigators said thieves have targeted cars parked near The 
Broadway in the south lot of the mall. Both vehicles and car stereos have been 
stolen. 
</P>
<P>
 The thefts occurred July 2, 7 and 9. The stereos were stolen around noon, 
while thieves waited until after 8 p.m. to take the cars, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators are asking anyone with information about the crimes to call 
Crime Stoppers at 494-TALK. Callers may remain anonymous. If the information 
leads to an arrest, the caller will receive $1,000. MARY F. POLS 
