<HEADLINE>
<P>
COWBOYS' SMITH SUFFERS MINOR INJURY WHEN CART STRIKES UNOFFICIAL MASCOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dallas Cowboy running back Emmitt Smith suffered a slight head injury Sunday 
when a small motorized cart he was riding ran into unofficial team mascot Ray 
Jones, 63, known as "Crazy Ray." 
</P>
<P>
 Smith, last season's regular-season and Super Bowl most valuable player, 
underwent a CAT scan at St. David Hospital. Test results were negative and 
Smith was released. Jones was not seriously injured. 
</P>
<P>
 The accident occurred shortly after noon as players gathered at the Cowboys' 
training camp on the campus of St. Edward's University. Smith was riding a cart 
driven by teammate Tommie Agee when they hit Jones. 
</P>
</TEXT>
