</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Thousands of Americans pocketed more than $1.8 billion in food-stamp benefits 
they were not entitled to receive last year -- a record loss that the 
Agriculture Department blames on mistakes and fraud. 
</P>
<P>
 In a recent letter to key members of Congress, the Agriculture Department said 
that 8.29% of food-stamp benefits went to people who were ineligible or 
collected more than they were entitled. 
</P>
