<P>
 Remittances From Abroad Up 9.7%: The amount of money sent home from abroad by 
residents of the Philippines rose 9.7% in the first four months of the year, 
helping make the peso stronger against the dollar.Remittances are likely to 
accelerate in the second half of the year. Analysts said remittances usually 
surge in the last quarter of the year when Filipinos living abroad send home 
more money as Christmas gifts to their families. The Bangko Sentral ng 
Pilipinas said remittances from January to April totaled $794.9 million, up 
$70.5 million from a year ago. At that pace, total remittances will surpass 
$2.5 billion for the whole year. In 1993, $2.3 billion was remitted through 
banks. 
