<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA ANA; SHOOTING AT PARTY CLAIMS MAN'S LIFE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 One man was shot to death and another wounded when violence erupted at a party 
advertised by flyer, police said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Witnesses told police that a party in the 1600 block of South Sycamore Street 
was disrupted when a fight broke out and two young men began shooting at each 
other about 3:50 p.m. Saturday, Santa Ana Police Cpl.Jeff Armstrong said. 
</P>
<P>
 Michael Valenzuela, 19, of Santa Ana was shot once in the chest and was 
pronounced dead at Western Medical Center in Santa Ana, Armstrong said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police were later called to the 1400 block of South Main Street, about three 
blocks away, where a second fight had broken out, Armstrong said. 
</P>
<P>
 "They were the same individuals involved in the fight on South Sycamore," 
Armstrong said. 
</P>
<P>
 No suspects were arrested at the Main Street address but police said they 
found a pistol believed to have been used in the gun battle. 
</P>
<P>
 Police later learned that another man had sought medical attention at Coastal 
Community Hospital for a minor injury from a gunshot wound, Armstrong said. It 
was unclear whether the second man had been shot at the first party or the 
second. 
</P>
<P>
 Armstrong said the shootings are being investigated as a gang-related 
incidents. 
</P>
