<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ORANGE; HEARING TO FOCUS ON AFFORDABLE HOUSING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LESLEY WRIGHT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Planning Commission will have a public hearing at 7 tonight to discuss an 
affordable housing plan. 
</P>
<P>
 The voluntary plan, which eventually will be part of the development review 
process, relies on incentives for builders to include affordable housing in 
their projects. 
</P>
<P>
 The plan's goal is to make 20% of new housing affordable for low- to 
moderate-income families. 
</P>
<P>
 The incentives available to developers include the ability to build more homes 
than otherwise would be allowed and the right to use modular homes. 
</P>
<P>
 The commission meets in council chambers at City Hall, 300 E. Chapman 
Ave.LESLEY WRIGHT 
