<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LAGUNA NIGUEL; NOMINATION PAPERS FOR 2 SEATS AVAILABLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LYNN FRANEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nomination papers for two City Council seats to be contested in the November 
election will be available beginning today. 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Niguel residents who wish to run for the seats held by council members 
Patricia C. Bates and James F. Krembas have until 5 p.m. Aug. 12 to file 
nomination papers. 
</P>
<P>
 Nomination papers must be signed by 20 to 30 registered Laguna Niguel voters. 
</P>
<P>
 City Clerk Juanita Zarilla recommends that potential candidates gather the 
maximum number of signatures in case any are deemed invalid. 
</P>
<P>
 Voters may sign the nomination papers of only two potential candidates. 
</P>
<P>
 Candidates must also submit a statement of economic interests along with the 
signatures. 
</P>
<P>
 For a $750 fee, candidates may also turn in a personal statement to be placed 
in the sample ballot. 
</P>
<P>
 Council members earn a $400 monthly stipend. 
</P>
<P>
 The forms may be picked up at the city clerk's office, 27801 La Paz Road. 
</P>
<P>
 If an incumbent does not file nomination papers by the Aug. 12 deadline, the 
filing period will be extended to Aug. 17. LYNN FRANEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
